  "texts": [
    "As the research was looking for key principles and normative attributes that could form a common ground for the comparison of HE policies, this vast set of documents was used to identify internationally recognised bodies that have potential real influence in this arena and decided to consider the guidelines and recommendations they have put forward for the ethical governance of AI.",
    "Therefore, for the purpose of this study, the following sources were selected (some organisations, such as the EU were represented by several bodies):",
    "-European Commission (2021): Regulation of the European Parliament and of the Council Laying Down Harmonised Rules on Artificial Intelligence (Artificial Intelligence Act) and Amending Certain Union Legislative Acts (2021/0106 (COD)).",
    "4 -European Parliament Committee on Culture and Education (2021): Report on artificial intelligence in education, culture and the audiovisual sector (2020/2017(INI)).",
    "5 -High-Level Expert Group on Artificial Intelligence (EUHLEX) (2019): Ethics Guidelines for Trustworthy AI."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}